      <item>
        <title>Escape from Tarkov: Yes! GNU/Linux runs it!</title>
        <link>https://sim590.github.io/en/gaming-on-linux/tarkov/</link>
        <pubDate>Sat, 12 Feb 2022 09:57:51 -0500</pubDate>
        <author>sim.desaulniers@gmail.com (Simon Désaulniers)</author>
        <atom:modified>Sat, 12 Feb 2022 09:57:51 -0500</atom:modified>
        <guid>https://sim590.github.io/en/gaming-on-linux/tarkov/</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Escape from Tarkov is hyper-realistic first person shooter game including survival, weapon
personalization, looting and questing mechanics. It is a well-known game which has been available to
play since 2016. However this game has stayed in Beta state since then, it is perfectly correct to
call this game full featured.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://sim590.github.io/images/Escape-from-Tarkov-header.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;EFT_splash&#34; title=&#34;Escape from Tarkov Splash Screen&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yes, the title says that GNU/Linux runs EFT (Escape from Tarkov), but does that mean that &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.battlestategames.com/&#34;&gt;BSG&lt;/a&gt;
(BattleStateGames), the game studio, has made a fully supported Linux port? Well, no. But that is
not surprising at all!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
        
